                      <item xml:id="e7">
                        <locus target="#34v #38r #103r" facs="035 038 103"> f. 34v, 38r, 103r and passim</locus>
                        <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the
                          scribe completes the line of text below or above the end of the line (throughout). The scribe generally will complete above the line when
                          dealing with the bottom margin
                        </desc>
